# 🎯 Number Guessing Game — Java

> **DecodeLabs Industrial Training Kit | Batch 2026 | Project 1**

A console-based number guessing game built in Java that demonstrates core programming concepts including control flow, user interaction, exception handling, and score tracking.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

The program generates a random number between **1 and 100** and challenges the player to guess it within a limited number of attempts. After each guess, it provides directional feedback (too high / too low) to guide the player toward the answer.

This project was built as **Project 1** of the DecodeLabs Java Programming track, focusing on:
- Program state management
- Real-time user input handling
- Defensive (crash-proof) engineering

---

## ✨ Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Random Number Generation | Uses `java.util.Random` to pick a number from 1–100 each round |
| High / Low Feedback | Tells the player whether each guess is too high or too low |
| Attempt Limiter | Player gets 7 attempts per round (solvable via binary search) |
| Score Tracking | Points are awarded based on how few attempts were used |
| Multiple Rounds | Player can replay as many rounds as they want |
| Input Validation | `try-catch` handles non-integer input without crashing |

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Language:** Java (JDK 8+)
- **Libraries:** `java.util.Random`, `java.util.Scanner`
- **IDE:** Any (IntelliJ IDEA / VS Code / Eclipse)

---

## 🚀 How to Run

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/number-guessing-game-java.git
cd number-guessing-game-java
```

### 2. Compile
```bash
javac DecodeLabs_Java_P1.java
```

### 3. Run
```bash
java DecodeLabs_Java_P1
```

